	"title": "Au restaurant — Food & drink",
	"objective": "Order food and drink and say what you like (A1: can order a meal and express simple preferences).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: « du / de la » means “some”",
		"body": "To ask for an unspecified amount, French uses the partitive: **du** (masc.), **de la** (fem.), **des** (plural) — “some”. **Je voudrais du thé** = “I’d like some tea.” Hindi and English often drop “some” (मुझे चाय चाहिए / “I’d like tea”), so remember to add it in French. ⚠️ Faux-ami: **une entrée** is a *starter*, not the main dish."
	},
